analysis: The documents primarily concern adjustments to the pay and compensation structures for various categories of federal employees, including those in the General Schedule, Foreign Service, Veterans Health Administration, Senior Executive Service, uniformed services, and the Executive, Legislative, and Judicial branches. They specify rates of basic pay, allowances, and locality-based comparability payments. The documents also delegate authority for prescribing rules and regulations related to these pay adjustments.
title: Federal Employee Compensation Schedules
